The farthest element from 0 can be on the negative side or positive side of a number line.

You need to sort it using `Arrays.sort(arr)` This method internally uses the dual-pivot quicksort method which has the time complexity of `O(nlog(n))` and obviously constant space complexity. Then compare the absolute value of first and last element and return the larger one.

