Based on your error message, the problem is that you are trying to send the data that cannot be parsed into your enum. The way things works is that first, your request body is parsed into the `CourseRequest` class, and then ***if*** the parsing is successful -- Bean Validation will apply.
 
If you want to use Bean Validation for checking that the string sent is valid - consider changing the `CourseRequest` where instead of an enum make that field a `String` this way parsing will not fail. Then you can use a `@Pattern` constraint to apply a regex check to that field to make sure that only acceptable strings are sent.

Then you can just have a getter in your `CourseRequest` that would convert the string to an enum to use it elsewhere:

```java
class CourseRequest {
	@Pattern(regexp = &quot;^(PENDING|CANCELED)$&quot;)
	String status;

	public CourseStatus courseStatus() {
		return status == null ? null : CourseStatus.valueOf( status );
	}
}
```

